genresAdvancedInfo.name: classic danish rock
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Classic Danish rock is a genre of rock music that originated in Denmark in the 1960s. It is characterized by its heavy use of electric guitars, powerful vocals, and introspective lyrics. Classic Danish rock bands such as Gasolin' and Kim Larsen have achieved legendary status in Denmark and continue to inspire new generations of musicians.
